-- Praktiker’s Biggest Holder Wants Part of Company Sold, FTD Says
-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 2012-03-27T06:41:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/praktiker-s-biggest-holder-wants-part-of-company-sold-ftd-says.html
Praktiker AG (PRA) ’s largest shareholder,
Maseltov Ltd., wants the company to sell its business in eastern
 Europe  as part of a reorganization, the  Financial Times
Deutschland  reported, citing Isabella de Krassny, a  fund manager 
and spokeswoman for Maseltov.  A sale could bring Praktiker, a home-improvement retailer,
50 million euros to 70 million euros ($67 million to $93
million), the FTD said. Maseltov owns 10 percent of the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julie Cruz in Frankfurt via 
